name: earth
description: Earth is the third planet from the Sun and the home-world of humanity.

name: mars
description: Mars is the fourth planet from the Sun and the second-smallest planet in the Solar System, being larger than only Mercury.

meta_data.title: Mars
meta_data.motivation: Mars can easily be seen from Earth with the naked eye, as can its reddish coloring.

name: ceres
description: Ceres is the largest object in the main asteroid belt that lies between the orbits of Mars and Jupiter.

name: venus
description: Venus is the second planet from the Sun. It is named after the Roman goddess of love and beauty.

meta_data.title: Venus
meta_data.motivation: Venus lies within Earth's orbit, and so never appears to venture far from the Sun, either setting in the west just after dusk or rising in the east a bit before dawn.

name: Phoebe
description: Phoebe is an irregular satellite of Saturn. It was spherical and hot early in its history and was battered out of roundness by repeated impacts.

name: europa
description: Europa is the smallest of the four Galilean moons orbiting Jupiter, and the sixth-closest to the planet of all the 79 known moons of Jupiter.

name: neptune
description: Neptune is the eighth and farthest-known Solar planet from the Sun. In the Solar System, it is the fourth-largest planet by diameter, the third-most-massive planet, and the densest giant planet.

name: auberon
description: Auberon is a planet that has a lush biome that grows native and Terran crops.

name: uranus
description: Uranus is the seventh planet from the Sun. Its name is a reference to the Greek god of the sky.

name: herculina
description: Herculina is one of the larger members of the main asteroid belt.

name: ganymede
description: Ganymede is the largest and most massive of the Solar System's moons.

name: luna
description: Moon is an astronomical body orbiting Earth and is the planet's only natural satellite.

name: laconia
description: Laconia is an evil planet in the system with the same name.

name: gate
description: A wormhole gate that is part of an ancient network built by an alien civilization billions of years ago.

name: naraka
description: The Naraka system is a dead system connected to the Ring network.

name: eros
description: Eros is a stony and elongated asteroid of the Amor group.

name: pluto
description: Pluto is a dwarf planet in the Kuiper belt, a ring of bodies beyond the orbit of Neptune.

name: mimas
description: Mimas, also designated Saturn I, is a moon of Saturn which was discovered in 1789 by William Herschel.

name: enceladus
description: Enceladus is the sixth-largest moon of Saturn.

name: cyllene
description: Cyllene, also known as Jupiter XLVIII, is a natural satellite of Jupiter.

name: sol
description: The Sun is the star at the center of the Solar System.

name: saturn
description: Saturn's famous feature is its prominent ring system, which is composed mostly of ice particles, with a smaller amount of rocky debris and dust.

name: pallas
description: Pallas is the second asteroid to have been discovered, after 1 Ceres.

name: iapetus
description: Iapetus is the third-largest natural satellite of Saturn, eleventh-largest in the Solar System.

name: mercury
description: Mercury is the smallest and innermost planet in the Solar System.

name: hungaria
description: Hungaria is a relatively small asteroid orbiting in the inner asteroid belt.

name: arcadia
description: The Arcadia system is one of the planetary systems connected to the Ring network. It was colonized by humans after this ancient network of wormhole gates was re-established by the Ring Station.

name: Jupiter/io
description: Io is the innermost and third-largest of the four Galilean moons of the planet Jupiter.

name: eugenia
description: Eugenia is a large asteroid of the asteroid belt.

name: ilus
description: Ilus is a large Earth-like planet, with slightly over one gravity and a thirty-hour day.

name: deimos
description: Deimos is the smaller and outermost of the two natural satellites of Mars, the other being Phobos.

name: jupiter
description: Jupiter is the fifth planet from the Sun and the largest in the Solar System.

name: rhea
description: Rhea is the second-largest moon of Saturn and the ninth-largest moon in the Solar System.

name: tecoma
description: The Tecoma system was one of the dead systems that was connected to the Ring network.

name: vesta
description: Vesta is one of the largest objects in the asteroid belt.

name: phobos
description: Phobos is the innermost and larger of the two natural satellites of Mars.

name: oshima
description: Oshima is a Veritasian asteroid from the outer regions of the asteroid belt.

name: charon
description: The Charon system is a dead system connected to the Ring network. Very little is known about this system.

name: callisto
description: Callisto is the second-largest moon of Jupiter, after Ganymede.

name: adro
description: The Adro system has a faint white dwarf star and no planets.
